# Orator clang-tidy: a curated, low-noise SAFETY gate for C++ translation units
# (.cc). Governance rationale (Constitution Art. V):
#
# - readability-identifier-naming is intentionally NOT enabled. The codebase
#   uses a consistent but MIXED method style (PascalCase actions like Register()
#   alongside lower_case accessors like name()/valid()/to_string()) plus
#   UPPER_CASE enum constants; one clang-tidy rule cannot express that, so
#   enforcing it would mass-rename ~7.5k identifiers for no behavior gain.
#   Naming stays consistent by review against the existing patterns.
# - Noisy/low-value checks are disabled: performance-enum-size (micro-opt),
#   bugprone-casting-through-void (the RAII GpuBuffer::data()->void*->cast
#   idiom), bugprone-macro-parentheses (CUDA_CHECK-style macros), and the
#   swappable/narrowing families.
# - .cu/.cuh are excluded (nvcc-compiled; clang-tidy's CUDA frontend differs).
Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  misc-definitions-in-headers,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-narrowing-conversions,
  -bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result,
  -bugprone-reserved-identifier,
  -bugprone-casting-through-void,
  -bugprone-macro-parentheses,
  -performance-enum-size,
  -performance-avoid-endl

WarningsAsErrors: ''
HeaderFilterRegex: '(include|src)/.*\.h$'
FormatStyle: file
